# finhq-verse Study Guide

**Author:** Learning documentation for experienced Java developer
**Started:** December 2024
**Status:** In Progress

---

## About This Guide

This study guide is designed for an experienced Java developer (10+ years) who is new to the finhq domain. It skips basic Java/Spring concepts and focuses on finhq-specific patterns and architecture.

## Directory Structure

```
docs/study-guide/
├── README.md                    # This file - overview and progress tracking
├── PROGRESS.md                  # Learning progress tracker with checkboxes
├── architecture/
│   ├── 01-overview.md           # High-level system architecture
│   ├── 02-monorepo-structure.md # Nx monorepo organization
│   └── 03-service-topology.md   # Service dependencies and communication
├── patterns/
│   ├── 01-passport-pattern.md   # Multi-tenancy via Passport
│   ├── 02-repository-pattern.md # Custom Repository<T> interface
│   ├── 03-service-pattern.md    # AbstractService template
│   ├── 04-entity-pattern.md     # Entity hierarchy and auditing
│   └── 05-error-handling.md     # ApplicationException pattern
├── services/
│   ├── 01-foundation.md         # Foundation service deep-dive
│   ├── 02-bookkeeping.md        # Bookkeeping service deep-dive
│   ├── 03-calendar.md           # Calendar service deep-dive
│   ├── 04-configuration.md      # Configuration service deep-dive
│   ├── 05-consumer.md           # Consumer service deep-dive
│   └── 06-settlement.md         # Settlement service deep-dive
├── examples/
│   ├── 01-creating-entity.md    # How to create a new entity
│   ├── 02-adding-api.md         # How to add a new API endpoint
│   └── 03-common-tasks.md       # Common development tasks
